cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

The paper focuses on the development and testing of a deep-learning based approach for the analysis of ocean eddies using convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of state-of-the-art image processing tools and object tracking methods, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the identification and tracking of ocean eddies, which can be considered as a robotics and control problem (cs.RO) and a graphics-related problem (cs.GR).
